      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that religious freedom is an absolute right that supersedes all state laws is a highly contested philosophical position. While religious freedom is a deeply held value, it is not absolute when it directly infringes upon the fundamental rights or safety of others. A fair society must operate under the principle that individual rights can and must be limited when they conflict with the collective good protected by secular law.",
      "source": "target",
